snippet: As imposing as the United States Olympic swimming team looks on paper, success in the trials will not automatically translate into gold medals at the London Games.
abstract: Karen Crouse On Swimming column observes that while the United States has assembled a formidable team for the 2012 London games, performances at trials and current world rankings do not always predict Olympic winners.
lead_paragraph: As imposing as the United States Olympic swimming team looks on paper, success in the trials will not automatically translate into gold medals at the London Games.

headline.seo: Beyond Trials, U.S. Swim Team Will Find Triumphs Harder to Come By
